%% Pudel DPoP (RFC 9449) Flow vWorld Standard.group
%% Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Vue Frontend
    participant Crypto as Web Crypto API
    participant API as Pudel API
    participant Filter as JwtAuthenticationFilter
    participant DPoP as DPoPService
    participant JWT as JwtUtil
    participant Discord as Discord OAuth2

    Note over Client,Discord: Step 1: Generate Client Keypair (one-time)

    Client->>Crypto: generateKey("RSA-PSS" or "ECDSA")
    Crypto-->>Client: { publicKey, privateKey }
    Client->>Client: Store keypair in browser

    Note over Client,Discord: Step 2: DPoP-Bound Token Request

    Client->>Client: Create DPoP proof JWT
    Note right of Client: Header: { typ: "dpop+jwt",<br/>alg: "RS256", jwk: publicKey }<br/>Payload: { jti: uuid, htm: "POST",<br/>htu: "/api/auth/discord/callback",<br/>iat: now }
    Client->>Crypto: sign(proof, privateKey)
    Crypto-->>Client: signed DPoP proof

    Client->>API: POST /api/auth/discord/callback
    Note right of Client: DPoP: <proof JWT><br/>Body: { code: "oauth_code" }

    API->>DPoP: validateProofForTokenRequest(proof, "POST", uri)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Verify proof signature (from JWK in header)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate jti uniqueness (replay check)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate htm = "POST"
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate htu matches URI
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate iat (within 5min, ±30s skew)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Calculate JWK thumbprint (RFC 7638)
    DPoP-->>API: ✓ thumbprint = "abc123..."

    API->>Discord: Exchange code for access token
    Discord-->>API: Discord user info

    API->>JWT: generateDPoPBoundToken(userId, claims, thumbprint)
    Note right of JWT: JWT contains cnf.jkt = thumbprint
    JWT-->>API: DPoP-bound JWT

    API->>DPoP: bindTokenToThumbprint(jwt, thumbprint)
    API-->>Client: { token: "...", token_type: "DPoP" }

    Note over Client,Discord: Step 3: Protected Resource Access

    Client->>Client: Create fresh DPoP proof
    Note right of Client: Payload: { jti: new_uuid,<br/>htm: "GET",<br/>htu: "/api/guilds/123/settings",<br/>iat: now,<br/>ath: SHA256(access_token) }
    Client->>Crypto: sign(proof, privateKey)
    Crypto-->>Client: fresh proof

    Client->>Filter: GET /api/guilds/123/settings
    Note right of Client: Authorization: DPoP <token><br/>DPoP: <fresh proof>

    Filter->>Filter: Detect "DPoP" auth scheme
    Filter->>JWT: validateToken(token)
    JWT-->>Filter: ✓ valid

    Filter->>DPoP: validateProofForResource(proof, "GET", uri, token)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Verify proof signature
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate jti (not replayed)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate htm = "GET"
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate htu matches URI
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate iat (fresh)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Validate ath = SHA256(token)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Verify thumbprint matches binding
    DPoP-->>Filter: ✓ valid

    Filter->>Filter: Set auth: [USER, DPOP_VERIFIED]
    Filter-->>Client: 200 OK + guild settings

    Note over Client,Discord: Error: Stolen Token (no private key)
        Note over Client,Filter: Attacker intercepts DPoP-bound token
        Client->>Filter: GET /api/guilds/123/settings
        Note right of Client: Authorization: Bearer <stolen_token>
        Filter->>JWT: isDPoPBoundToken(token)
        JWT-->>Filter: true (has cnf.jkt claim)
        Filter-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized
        Note right of Filter: WWW-Authenticate: DPoP<br/>error="use_dpop_nonce"<br/>"Token is DPoP-bound"

    Note over Client,Discord: Logout

    Client->>API: POST /api/auth/logout
    Note right of Client: Authorization: DPoP <token><br/>DPoP: <proof>
    API->>DPoP: revokeTokenBinding(token)
    DPoP->>DPoP: Remove tokenBindings[token]
    API-->>Client: 200 OK

